When we can label attachments (CONF-3963), we should also be able to list them by labels. ALSO by no labels.

This will increase the usefulness of the \{attachment} macro. We may then label attachments and have section in the document for e.g. contracts, orders, etc. and other documents (attachments without any labels).

In the notation guide, the following example is displayed under the {{\{page-info\}}} macro:

{noformat}
{page-info:displaytype|page=Home|dateformat:ddMMYY HHmm}
{noformat}

It appears that the parameter {{dateformat}} defined is invalid. The valid parameter should be {{dataFormat}}. Also note that colon, ":" is used instead of the "=" to define the parameter's value in the Notation guide. Hence, a suggestion of the example used should be:
{noformat}
{page-info:displaytype|page=Home|dateFormat=ddMMYY HHmm}
{noformat}
